<item>
            <title>[MJAVADOC-45] Quoted argument text must escape apostrophes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-45</link>
                <project id="12317529" key="MJAVADOC">Maven Javadoc Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The default -bottom argument passed to javadoc looks like this for me:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-bottom &apos;Copyright 2006 Brian S O&apos;Neill. All Rights Reserved.&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The apostrophe in my name is breaking the quoted string, and javadoc dies. I can workaround this by passing the bottom argument in pom.xml, escaping the apostrophe with a backslash.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The javadoc plugin should escape all quoted arguments. It seems pretty easy, just change the quotedArgument method.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Win2k</environment>
